LitCode 0.2.201

* Split between actual source code and Examples
A person using literate programming might not be interested in using LaTeX; they might be using in more shiny
tools like Markdown or Asciidoc or whatever. And it is understandable: not every gun makes the same tune.
Therefore, in this version, I have put the examples separately in an `examples` directory, away from the
source files. Makefile has also been changed. At present, no examples are being either tangled or weaved. 

* Cosmetic changes to the documentation: Font-size of 9pt, and geometry of the margins has  been reset.
  Furthermore, background of code is now white and not yellow. 

* PDF doc won't be converted to HTML.